The Spanish health service is administered by each autonomous region, which means there are marked differences in the actual state of the service.
A chain of infections among health workers aggravated the situation, until many of them were forced to go into quarantine.
The Catalan President, Quim Torra, was publicly attacked by Spanish ministers for wanting to go further than the Spanish state by completely sealing off and closing down Catalonia.
The centralization of power in the Spanish state during the crisis is a reflection of the outlook of the capitalist class.
Yet the need for real international solidarity and cooperation to fight the COVID-19 virus is there for all to see.